            "summary": "Prominent figures in the cryptocurrency industry, including World Liberty Financial and Binance, are responding to accusations that they collaborated on promoting a decentralized finance project linked to former President Donald Trump. The dispute arose after claims were made in a Wall Street Journal article suggesting that Binance's founder, Changpeng Zhao, had supported international initiatives for the DeFi platform. According to a report by The Block released on Friday, Zak Folkman, one of the co-founders of World Liberty Financial (WLFI), took to social media to strongly deny these allegations. Folkman refuted any insinuation that Zhao, also known as \"CZ,\" played a hidden role in aiding WLFI or its co-founder, Zach Witkoff, emphasizing that the notion was baseless and false. The Wall Street Journal had hinted at potential ties between Zhao and WLFI's activities aimed at expanding into countries like Pakistan. More details can be found on Benzinga.com.",
